name: What Lies Before Me? 2008
description:
Jelly fish and metaphysical collage 
8 x 8" Birch wood Panel Digitized 2021
Exhibition the series at A.O.T.Gallery Port Townsend April 2008

"The art of Anne Marie Grgich feeds on, and grows strength from, accumulation. She piles image upon image. Sometimes words upon words. For the last couple of decades, collage has been the primary architecture of an Anne Grgich artwork. Back at the turn of the century, collaged elements often acted as a kind of base superstructure or foundation for her iconic painted figures. These images were sealed in complex layers of resin and paint that created enigmatic depths. Collage and painted lines and shapes existed in an easy inter-relationship from which visual meaning emerged."-Colin Rhodes 2019
